Face Mask Detector

📁 Project Structure
face-mask-detection/
│
├── deep_learning.ipynb          # Main training notebook
├── mask_detector_cnn_best.h5   # Saved best model (generated after training)
├── label_map.json              # Index-to-label mapping {0: "with_mask", 1: "without_mask"}
├── deploy.prototxt             # OpenCV DNN SSD face detector config
├── res10_300x300_ssd_iter_140000.caffemodel  # Pre-trained face detector weights
└── README.md

📦 Dataset

Source: Kaggle — Face Mask Dataset by omkargurav
Classes: 2

with_mask — ~3725 images
without_mask — ~3828 images


Folder structure expected:
data/
  with_mask/
    image1.jpg
    image2.jpg
    ...
  without_mask/
    image1.jpg
    ...
pip install tensorflow keras numpy matplotlib scikit-learn opencv-python kagglehub

GPU recommended. Notebook is optimized for Kaggle P100. Mixed precision (float16) is enabled for speed.

🚀 How to Run
Step 1 — Download Dataset
pythonimport kagglehub
path = kagglehub.dataset_download("omkargurav/face-mask-dataset")
Step 2 — Train the Model
Run all cells in deep_learning.ipynb. The notebook will:

Load and augment images via ImageDataGenerator
Build and compile the CNN
Train with EarlyStopping (max 30 epochs)
Save the best model to mask_detector_cnn_best.h5

Step 3 — Run Inference
out = robust_predict("/path/to/your/image.jpg", show=True)
print(out)
# {'status': 'ok', 'method': 'dnn_ssd', 'predictions': [{'box': [...], 'label': 'with_mask', 'confidence': 0.97}]}
